<HEADLINE>
FT  02 OCT 93 / World News in Brief: Cars recalled
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Ford is recalling 57,000 Mondeo saloons in Britain because of a small defect
in the handbrake lever. The right-hand drive cars were made between in
Belgium between March and June this year.
</TEXT>
